DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260718T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260718T203000
DTSTAMP:20260617T232446
CREATED:20240405T174500Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260421T213909Z
UID:10000918-1784399400-1784406600@houstonarboretum.org
SUMMARY:Opossums & Popsicles
DESCRIPTION:$37 member / $52 nonmember / $22 children ages 5-12Instructor: Wildlife Center of TexasAges 5+ \n\n\n\nChill out with some of the coolest critters around! Grab a frozen treat\, enjoy a refreshing root beer (or regular beer) from Saint Arnold Brewing Company\, and get up close and personal with live wild animals from Wildlife Center of Texas. You’ll learn all about Houston’s amazing urban wildlife – including opossums – and then you’ll go on a guided hike to enjoy a truly wild night out. \n\n\n\nPlease dress for the weather and wear walking shoes \n\n\n\n\nRegister online\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nInstructor Bio: The Wildlife Center of Texas is one of the largest rehabilitation centers in the country\, admitting nearly 10\,000 wild patients each year. Its mission is to care for all injured\, orphaned\, ill\, and oiled wildlife through wildlife rehabilitation\, public education\, and oiled wildlife response.
URL:https://houstonarboretum.org/event/opossums-popsicles/
CATEGORIES:Family Programs
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://houstonarboretum.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Opossum-AdobeStock.jpg
END:VEVENT
